#. <section class="sutta" id="sn52.7"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn52.7:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 52"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 52"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn52.7:0.2"
msgid "1. Rahogatavagga"
msgstr "1. In Private"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 7. Taṇhākkhayasutta → taṇhakkhayasuttaṃ (bj) | taṇhakkhaya (pts1)
msgctxt "sn52.7:0.3"
msgid "7. Taṇhākkhayasutta"
msgstr "7. The Ending of Craving"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli5.300"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn52.7:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn52.7:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho āyasmā anuruddho bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There Venerable Anuruddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "sn52.7:1.3"
msgid "“āvuso bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Reverends, mendicants!”"

msgctxt "sn52.7:1.4"
msgid "“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato anuruddhassa paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Reverend,” they replied."

msgctxt "sn52.7:1.5"
msgid "Āyasmā anuruddho etadavoca:"
msgstr "Anuruddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: taṇhākkhayāya → taṇhakkhayāya (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "sn52.7:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Cattārome, āvuso, satipaṭṭhānā bhāvitā bahulīkatā taṇhākkhayāya saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"“Reverends, when these four kinds of mindfulness meditation are developed "
"and cultivated they lead to the ending of craving."

msgctxt "sn52.7:2.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn52.7:2.3"
msgid "Idhāvuso, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati … pe …"
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body …"

msgctxt "sn52.7:2.4"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe …"
msgstr "feelings …"

msgctxt "sn52.7:2.5"
msgid "citte … pe …"
msgstr "mind …"

msgctxt "sn52.7:2.6"
msgid ""
"dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the "
"world."

msgctxt "sn52.7:2.7"
msgid ""
"ime kho, āvuso, cattāro satipaṭṭhānā bhāvitā bahulīkatā taṇhākkhayāya "
"saṃvattantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"When these four kinds of mindfulness meditation are developed and cultivated "
"they lead to the ending of craving.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn52.7:2.8"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
